'''Starhunter's Intergalactic Menagerie''' was a traveling [[Circus/Legends|circus]] and rarity show, owned by Captain [[Stroon]] and his assistant, [[Slarm (Human)|Slarm]].

==History==
[[File:Starhunters.jpg|right|thumb|Alien and Human personnel of the Starhunters Intergalactic Menagerie.]]Touring the [[The galaxy|galaxy]] during the [[Imperial Era/Legends|early days]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]],<ref name=":0">''[[A Guide to the Star Wars Universe, Second Edition, Revised and Expanded]]''</ref> the Starhunter's Intergalactic Menagerie<ref name="CATS" /> was a traveling sideshow whose attractions were rare and usually illegally acquired creatures from many different worlds,<ref name=":0" /> and it moved from system to system in a huge [[Starship/Legends|cruiser]],<ref name="CATS" /> a [[Starhunter menagerie ark]].<ref>{{Hyperspace|url=fans/hyperspace/source/feature20081201.html|text=Castaways of Endor|int=Castaways of Endor}}</ref> The sideshow and ship were owned and operated by [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Stroon]],<ref name="CATS" /> while his [[First Mate/Legends|first mate]] and assistant<ref name=":0" /> was [[Slarm (Human)|Slarm]]. The "Starhunters"<ref name="CATS" /> were a crew of trackers<ref>{{SW|url=news/the-droids-re-animated-part-2|series=The Droids Re-Animated|text=Part 2|nolive=1}}</ref> made up of both [[Human/Legends|Humans]] and aliens. They could also specializing in [[Slavery/Legends|capturing]] intelligent lifeforms, such as the humanoid [[Greej]], who they would sell as "pets" to aliens in distant parts of the galaxy. They sometimes made a supply stop at [[Chuzalla]].<ref name="CATS" />

At some point the Starhunters came to [[Dandelo]],<ref name="CATS" /> a [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]].<ref name="AOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref> They drove the local [[Fuzzum|Fuzzums]] from their caves so as to convert the dwellings into cages to store rare beasts destined to join their traveling menagerie. From time to time, Fuzzums were spotted and captured by the Starhunters; these captives were then forced to use their skills as trappers and hunters to find more animals for the menagerie. Over time, the Starhunters began to actively seek out Fuzzums as well as non-sentient species, and the Fuzzums grew to hate these offworlders.<ref name="CATS" />

In [[15 BBY/Legends|15 BBY]]<ref name="Date">{{PolyhedronCite|170|Star Wars Droids: The Adventures of R2-D2 and C-3PO}} states that [[Star Wars: Droids: The Adventures of R2-D2 and C-3PO|''Star Wars: Droids'']] is set 15 years before [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']]. ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' places the events of '' A New Hope'' in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], meaning that ''Star Wars: Droids'' takes place in [[15 BBY/Legends|15 BBY]].</ref> [[Jann Tosh]] put them of out business after they had captured [[Ingey]], the pet of [[Coby]].<ref name="CATS">{{DroidsCite|Coby and the Starhunters}}</ref>

